title: For Sale:  Beretta 96D + DA/SA
postcontent: What I have for sale is a Beretta 96D in .40 S&W. The gun started as a police issue double action only. It has an incredibly smooth DAO trigger pull right at 8lbs. The gun comes equipped with night sights (about 20% life left, very dim) that can be sent in to have new tritium vials put in or the front sight drilled out for a fiber optic rod. I have also installed the factory sear and seat spring so that with the swap of a hammer you can turn the pistol into "slick slide" double/single action (no active saftey/decocker so the hammer has to be thumbed down to decock and still has firing pin block and is drop safe) With the standard hammer the trigger pulls become DA ~8.3 lbs SA ~4 lbs with the beretta D spring (common aftermarket swap on all berettas) the gun is incredibly accurate and very fun too shoot in both configurations with a slide action that's ball bearing smooth with no rattle. The gun was carried as a duty gun for armed security and will come with three 11rnd mags and a two mag carrier. Also included all internal parts to covnert from DAO to DA/SA (I will set up the gun in either configuration per buyers request and show process to chancge it over which is incredibly simple) a soft case, and 50 rounds of 180 grain target ammo. I have thouroughly enjoyed this gun and am letting it go to invest in other projects. This will make an amazing firearm for home defense, "truck gun", range shooter, or serve as a duty weapon again. The only flaw she has at the moment is the rubber grips began to dry rot and crumble so the gun currently has only non skid metal plates as place holders for grips. Factory grips can be ordered online for about $20 or you could choose to upgrade to some VZ or Wilson combat grips for a bit more. title: For Sale:  Pre Ban Norinco 56S-1
postcontent: Hi all,Looking to thin the herd.  I just dont shoot this thing like I used to and hate to see it sit.  I've owned the gun for about 5 years and have put maybe 100 rounds through it.  Purchased it from Lawmen's in SC and was told it was a police dept "buy back" and that it was confiscated at some point in it's life and sat in storage at the department until sold to Lawmen's.  If you are familiar with pre ban AK's then I don't really need to elaborate on this gun.  Google "Norinco 56S-1" for more info if not.  This gun was bulit at 66 factory in late 80's/early 90's.  I've seen various forum posts on how to tell exact date from serial # but I'm honestly not sure.  SILE Import. All numbers match, great shape overall, but NOT a safe queen.  I wrapped the stock in paracord and put a magpul grip on it to improve "shootability" (lol on an underfolding AK) but the wrap is easily removed and I have the original wood grip and screw.  Wood is all original and showing the most signs of wear.  Light scuffs and very light surface wear on the dust cover, front sight shroud, and receiver.  I have many many more pictures I can send you should you need more detail.  I have three Chinese mags (2 30rd and 1 5rd) that are also original.  No box or bayonet.  I'll throw in 80 rds of steel Tula ammo for free as I don't own anything else in 7.62x39.  In the essence of full disclosure, I don't need to sell this (I just want to) so I'm not going to entertain low ball offers.  I know how much these are worth and I think the price is fair considering the condition.  I see shooters on GB and Armslist for 1200-1500 and safe queens for 2000+ That being said I am open to fair offers.  If you want a $700 AK go to Cabelas and buy a Yugo N-Pap or Century whatever it is they make these days.  And no, I don't want to trade for anything.  Sorry to sound like a prick but this isn't my first rodeo on Armslist so I'd prefer to get that out of the way now.  Any questions please let me know.
